<body>
   <h1>Css Box Model Demonstration</h1>  
   <div class="box">
    <h3 class="margin">Margin</h3>
    <h3 class="border">Border</h3>
    <div class="box2">
    <h3>This is the content inside the box!</h3>
   </div>
   <h3 class="padding">padding</h3>
   </div>
   <p>This example demonstrates the CSS box model:</p>
   <div class="css">
    <li>
        <b>Content:</b>
        The White area in the center where the text is displayed
    </li>
    <li>
        <b>Padding:</b>
        The space between the content and the border(light gray)
    </li>
    <li>
        <b>Border</b>
        The solid blue line surrounding the box
    </li>
    <li>
        <b>Margin:</b>
        The space outside the bporder(moves the box away from other elements)
    </li>
   </div>

